---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "@components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
import Page from "@layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Page
  title="Box Timer â€“ How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time"
  description="A guide that show you how to set an interval timer with both work and rest time using the app Box Timer - Workout Timer"
  url="https://boxtimer.app/support/how-to-set-an-interval-timer-with-both-work-and-rest-time/"
>
  <Container innerClass={"flex-col items-center"}>
    <div class="w-full sm:w-9/12">
      <Breadcrumbs
        >How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time</Breadcrumbs
      >
      <h1 class="w-full text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-sans font-bold mb-8">
        How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time
      </h1>
      <p class="pb-8">
        This guide will show you how to set an interval timer with both work and
        rest time. This would be useful if you have a Tabata workout or any
        other workout where you have both work time and rest time each round.
      </p>
      <p
        class="w-full text-2xl lg:text-2xl font-sans font-bold mb-4 text-zinc-800"
      >
        Steps
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6">
        <li><h2>Open the app</h2></li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Edit timer in the top right of the screen</h2>
          <img
            src="/images/support/interval-work-rest/interval-step-2.webp"
            alt="The Box Timer app - How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time step 2"
            class="rounded-xl mt-8 mb-16"
          />
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Interval in the segment control for Type of timer</h2>
          <img
            src="/images/support/interval-work-rest/interval-step-3.webp"
            alt="The Box Timer app - How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time step 3"
            class="rounded-xl mt-8 mb-16"
          />
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Rounds to set the amount of rounds of the timer</h2>
          <i>In the example it's 5 rounds</i>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Minutes and Seconds to set the work duration of the timer</h2>
          <i>In the example it's 0 minutes and 45 seconds</i>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Minutes and Seconds to set the rest duration of the timer</h2>
          <i>In the example it's 0 minutes and 15 seconds</i>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>
            Tap the Countdown toggle button to make sure that it's on, if you
            wan't a countdown before the timer starts.
          </h2>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Save to save the current timer settings</h2>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h2>Tap Start to start the timer</h2>
          <img
            src="/images/support/interval-work-rest/interval-step-9.webp"
            alt="The Box Timer app - How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time step 9"
            class="rounded-xl mt-8 mb-16"
          />
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </Container>
  <Footer />
</Page>
